\v 3 \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w no|strong="G3367"\w* \w one|strong="G3367"\w* \w be|strong="G1519"\w* unsettled \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w afflictions|strong="G2347"\w*; \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w you|strong="G3754"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G1722"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w we|strong="G3754"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w appointed|strong="G2749"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w*.\f + \fr 3:3 \ft We are appointed to affliction in this life. How many sermons have you heard on this topic? If the Son learned obedience through suffering (Hebrews 5:8), how about us? “Whom the Lord loves He chastens, and scourges every son whom He receives” (Hebrews 12:6). Have you ever been scourged, literally? I have—I didn't enjoy it.\f*  
\v 4 \w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w*, \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w we|strong="G3754"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w with|strong="G4314"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w we|strong="G3754"\w* \w kept|strong="G2532"\w* \w telling|strong="G4302"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w advance|strong="G4302"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w we|strong="G3754"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w going|strong="G3195"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w afflicted|strong="G2346"\w*;\f + \fr 3:4 \ft It was all a calculated risk. The messengers had their eyes open and wanted to make sure their hearers went into their new life with \+nd their\+nd* eyes open—there were no misleading promises of peace and prosperity!\f* \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w happened|strong="G1096"\w*, \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w fact|strong="G3754"\w*, \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w*.  
