\v 8 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* rejecter \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* rejecting \w man|strong="G3756"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w very|strong="G2532"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w gave|strong="G1325"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*\f + \fr 4:8 \ft Instead of “you”, perhaps 4% of the Greek manuscripts have ‘us’ (as in AV and NKJV).\f* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w Holy|strong="G4151"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*.\f + \fr 4:8 \ft Paul is writing to people who have the Holy Spirit.\f*   
\s1 An impressive life style  
\p
