\ms1 Christ's second coming  
\s1 The Rapture\f + \fr 4:13 \ft This paragraph defines the Rapture: Jesus comes down into the atmosphere of this planet (‘clouds’) and collects all those who belong to Him; the bodies of those who have died physically will be resurrected and reunited with their spirits; those still living will not have to die (death is separation); all their bodies will be glorified; the Christ will have His Bride.\f*  
\p
\v 13 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w*, brothers, \w we|strong="G2532"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w want|strong="G2309"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w ignorant|strong="G3361"\w* \w about|strong="G4012"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* ‘\w fallen|strong="G2837"\w* \w asleep|strong="G2837"\w*’,\f + \fr 4:13 \ft This is a metaphor for dying.\f* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w grieve|strong="G3076"\w* \w like|strong="G2531"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w rest|strong="G3062"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w hope|strong="G1680"\w*.  
