\v 16 \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* Himself—\w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* commanding \w shout|strong="G2752"\w*,\f + \fr 4:16 \ft One is reminded of Jesus' words in John 5:25-29. In verse 25 He says ‘now is’, so He is speaking of the spiritually dead who need to listen to Him and receive spiritual life. But in verse 28 He speaks plainly of those ‘in the graves’—all the dead will be resurrected at Jesus' command, including the lost, who will then be condemned to the Lake. I take it that here in 4:16 Jesus resurrects only the “dead in Christ”, and He uses a commanding shout. To raise Lazarus He gave a loud shout (John 11:43), that might have carried half a mile; this one will be heard around the globe.\f* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* archangel'\w s|strong="G2962"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w*\f + \fr 4:16 \ft There is only one archangel or top angel; once Lucifer, now Michael.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'\w s|strong="G2962"\w* \w trumpet|strong="G4536"\w*—\w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w come|strong="G2597"\w* \w down|strong="G2597"\w* \w from|strong="G2597"\w* \w heaven|strong="G3772"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* rise \w first|strong="G4413"\w*;  
