\p
\v 14 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w we|strong="G1161"\w* \w exhort|strong="G3870"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, brothers: \w admonish|strong="G3560"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* disorderly, \w encourage|strong="G3870"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w fainthearted|strong="G3642"\w*, \w be|strong="G3956"\w* supportive \w of|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* weak, \w be|strong="G3956"\w* \w patient|strong="G3114"\w* \w toward|strong="G4314"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*.\f + \fr 5:14 \ft Notice that the response is appropriate to the occasion, or the need.\f*  
\v 15 \w See|strong="G3708"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w no|strong="G3361"\w* \w one|strong="G5100"\w* pays \w back|strong="G1519"\w* \w bad|strong="G2556"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w bad|strong="G2556"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w*,\f + \fr 5:15 \ft The term ‘bad’ is less strong than the term for malignant evil, so the reference is not to malignant activity.\f* \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w always|strong="G3842"\w* \w pursue|strong="G1377"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w good|strong="G3956"\w*, \w both|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w one|strong="G5100"\w* \w another|strong="G5100"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*.\f + \fr 5:15 \ft The verb ‘pursue’ does not suggest a passive attitude; we should be actively promoting the good for the society at large wherever we live. The result will be a better place to live.\f*  
\v 16 \w Rejoice|strong="G5463"\w* \w always|strong="G3842"\w*!  
\v 17 \w Pray|strong="G4336"\w* continually!  
\v 18 \w Give|strong="G2168"\w* \w thanks|strong="G2168"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w everything|strong="G3956"\w*, \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w is|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w will|strong="G2307"\w* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*.\f + \fr 5:18 \ft There are those who say we should give thanks \+nd for\+nd* everything, as distinct from \+nd in\+nd* everything. I doubt that our Lord in the garden of Gethsemane gave thanks for the suffering He was facing and already enduring. To give thanks \+nd in\+nd* a distressful situation is a declaration of confidence in God and His disposition of our affairs.\f*  
\v 19 \w Do|strong="G3361"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w quench|strong="G4570"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*!\f + \fr 5:19 \ft When you quench a lighted candle, you put out its light. To quench the Spirit is presumably to ‘put out’ or refuse His light, to suppress or ignore His voice when He speaks to us—this would include any rejection of the revealed will of God.\f*  
\v 20 \w Do|strong="G3361"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* disdain prophesies,  
\v 21 \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w test|strong="G1381"\w* \w everything|strong="G3956"\w*;\f + \fr 5:21 \ft All prophesy should be tested, but not disdained or rejected.\f* \w hold|strong="G2722"\w* \w on|strong="G1161"\w* \w to|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w good|strong="G2570"\w*.  
\v 22 Keep away \w from|strong="G4190"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w form|strong="G1491"\w* \w of|strong="G3956"\w* \w evil|strong="G4190"\w*!\f + \fr 5:22 \ft The evil here is aggressive, or malignant.\f*   
\s1 Complete sanctification  
\p
\v 23 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w peace|strong="G1515"\w* Himself sanctify \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w completely|strong="G3648"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2962"\w* \w whole|strong="G3648"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w soul|strong="G5590"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w body|strong="G4983"\w*\f + \fr 5:23 \ft I take it that the grammatical structure of this phrase, “the spirit and the soul and the body” (in Greek), demands a tripartite/trichotomous view of the human being. I confess that I have trouble imagining complete sanctification for the body, in this life.\f* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w preserved|strong="G5083"\w* blameless \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w coming|strong="G3952"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.  
\v 24 \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w calls|strong="G2564"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w*.   
\s1 Farewell  
\p
\v 25 Brothers, \w pray|strong="G4336"\w* \w for|strong="G4012"\w* \w us|strong="G2249"\w*.  
\v 26 Greet \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* brothers \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G1722"\w* holy \w kiss|strong="G5370"\w*.  
\v 27 \w I|strong="G3956"\w* \w adjure|strong="G3726"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w by|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w letter|strong="G1992"\w* \w be|strong="G3956"\w* read \w to|strong="G3956"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* holy brothers.\f + \fr 5:27 \ft To adjure by the Lord that the letter be read is tantamount to claiming inspiration for it. By extension, does not “all the holy brothers” include us?\f*  
\v 28 \w The|strong="G3588"\w* \w grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w of|strong="G5485"\w* \w our|strong="G2424"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w be|strong="G3588"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*. Amen.   